---
title: Tomato-y Tortelloni Soup with Baby Spinach and Sausage
description: Give the dishwasher a break tonight: all you need to put this recipe together is a pot and a couple of utensils for stirring and chopping. But just because it involves minimal effort doesn’t mean that it has minimal flavor. Loaded with cheesy tortelloni, slices of sweet sausage, tender spinach leaves, and a tomato-y broth, the soup brims and bubbles with plenty of filling, Italian-inspired flavors.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/tomato-y-tortelloni-soup-47668673.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/tomato-y-tortelloni-soup-5a7a2eadae08b52d2b47e082-91e13ca1.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tomato-y-tortelloni-soup-5a7a2eadae08b52d2b47e082
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 810 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1850 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1/2} (save the rest
for another use). Pick @basil{1/2%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems. Remove
casings from @sweet Italian pork sausage{2%links} (use the other link as you
like).

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add sausage, breaking up meat into pieces. Cook, tossing,
until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add onion, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
and @dried oregano{1%teaspoon} to #pot{}. Cook, tossing, until just softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce can}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and
2 1/2 cups water to pot. Stir, scraping up any browned bits on bottom. Bring
to a boil, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once soup is boiling and seasoned, reduce heat to medium and gently stir in
@cheese tortelloni{9%ounce}. Let cook until tender, about ~{8%minutes}.

Stir @baby spinach{5%ounce} and half the basil into pot and let wilt. Season
with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup},
remaining basil leaves, and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste).